   "source": [
    "# 03 — Molecular Dynamics Basics\n",
    "\n",
    "**Adaptive Multiscale Biological Simulation AI**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook walks through the core physics building blocks:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Lennard-Jones fluid** — pairwise interactions\n",
    "2. **Periodic boundary conditions (PBC)** — simulating bulk matter\n",
    "3. **Velocity-Verlet integration in NVE** — energy conservation check\n",
    "4. **Langevin thermostat** — temperature control via friction + noise\n",
    "5. **Andersen thermostat** — stochastic collisions\n",
    "6. **RDF (Radial Distribution Function)** — structure of the fluid\n",
    "7. **MSD (Mean Squared Displacement)** — diffusion behavior"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from src.core.potentials import lj_potential, lj_force, lj_potential_pbc, lj_force_pbc, RCUT, SIGMA, EPSILON\n",
    "from src.core.integrators import velocity_verlet, integrate_nve\n",
    "from src.core.observables import compute_kinetic_energy, compute_potential_energy, compute_temperature, compute_pressure, compute_energy, compute_rdf, compute_msd\n",
    "from src.core.ensemble import andersen_thermostat, langevin_thermostat\n",
    "from src.core.initialise import fcc_lattice, assign_velocities\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 13, 'figure.dpi': 150, 'savefig.dpi': 150})\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "print(f\"RCUT = {RCUT:.2f}σ\\nSIGMA = {SIGMA}\\nEPSILON = {EPSILON}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. The Lennard-Jones Potential\n",
    "\n",
    "The Lennard-Jones potential models pairwise interactions between neutral atoms:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$V(r) = 4\\epsilon \\left[ \\left(\\frac{\\sigma}{r}\\right)^{12} - \\left(\\frac{\\sigma}{r}\\right)^6 \\right]$$\n",
    "\n",
    "- The $(\\sigma/r)^{12}$ term: strong repulsion at short distances\n",
    "- The $(\\sigma/r)^6$ term: attractive van der Waals at longer distances\n",
    "- Minimum at $r_{min} = 2^{1/6} \\sigma \\approx 1.122\\sigma$\n",
    "- Force: $F(r) = -\\nabla V(r)$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Plot the LJ potential and force\n",
    "r = np.linspace(0.5, 5.0, 500)\n",
    "r2 = r ** 2\n",
    "\n",
    "V = lj_potential(r2)\n",
    "F = lj_force(r2)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1.plot(r, V, 'b-', linewidth=2)\n",
    "ax1.axhline(0, color='k', linestyle='--', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "ax1.axvline(2**(1/6), color='r', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='r_min = 2^(1/6)')\n",
    "ax1.axvline(RCUT, color='g', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='r_cut')\n",
    "ax1.set_xlabel('r (σ)')\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel('V(r) (ε)')\n",
    "ax1.set_title('Lennard-Jones Potential')\n",
    "ax1.legend()\n",
    "ax1.set_ylim(-1.2, 10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Force is negative gradient: F > 0 means repulsion\n",
    "ax2.plot(r, F, 'r-', linewidth=2)\n",
    "ax2.axhline(0, color='k', linestyle='--', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "ax2.axvline(2**(1/6), color='b', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='r_min')\n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel('r (σ)')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('F(r) (ε/σ)')\n",
    "ax2.set_title('Lennard-Jones Force')\n",
    "ax2.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('figs/03_lj_potential.png', bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Potential minimum: V_min = {lj_potential(2**(1/3)):.4f} ε (at r = {2**(1/6):.4f} σ)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Particle Initialization — FCC Crystal\n",
    "\n",
    "We start with an FCC lattice of Argon atoms (4 atoms per unit cell)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def create_lattice(n_particles, box_length, temperature):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Create an initialization strategy selector.\n",
    "    Can return:\n",
    "    - FCC lattice (solid phase)\n",
    "    - Random positions (gas/liquid phase)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    n_cells = int(np.ceil((n_particles / 4) ** (1/3)))\n",
    "    positions = fcc_lattice(n_cells, box_length)\n",
    "    positions = positions[:n_particles]\n",
    "    velocities = assign_velocities(n_particles, temperature)\n",
    "    return positions, velocities\n",
    "\n",
    "def create_gas(n_particles, box_length, temperature):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create particles in random positions (low-density gas).\"\"\"\n",
    "    positions = np.random.uniform(0, box_length, (n_particles, 3))\n",
    "    velocities = assign_velocities(n_particles, temperature)\n",
    "    return positions, velocities\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create both configurations\n",
    "n_atoms = 64\n",
    "box = 8.0\n",
    "T_target = 0.8  # Reduced temperature\n",
    "\n",
    "# FCC (crystal-like)\n",
    "pos_fcc, vel_fcc = create_lattice(n_atoms, box, T_target)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Gas (random, very low density)\n",
    "pos_gas, vel_gas = create_gas(n_atoms, box, T_target)\n",
    "box_gas = 16.0  # Larger box for gas (lower density)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"FCC: {n_atoms} atoms in box {box:.1f}\\n  Density = {n_atoms / box**3:.3f} σ⁻³\")\n",
    "print(f\"Gas: {n_atoms} atoms in box {box_gas:.1f}\\n  Density = {n_atoms / box_gas**3:.4f} σ⁻³\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. NVE Ensemble — Microcanonical (Energy Conservation)\n",
    "\n",
    "In the NVE ensemble (constant Number, Volume, Energy), the total energy should be conserved (to within numerical integration error).\n",
    "\n",
    "We use the Velocity-Verlet integrator:\n",
    "$$\\begin{align*}\n",
    "r(t+\\Delta t) &= r(t) + v(t)\\Delta t + \\frac{1}{2}a(t)\\Delta t^2 \\\\\n",
    "v(t+\\Delta t) &= v(t) + \\frac{1}{2}[a(t) + a(t+\\Delta t)]\\Delta t\n",
    "\\end{align*}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# NVE simulation parameters\n",
    "dt = 0.002       # Reduced time step\n",
    "n_steps = 5000   # Total steps\n",
    "stride = 50      # Save every 50 steps\n",
    "mass = 1.0\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Simulating 64-atom LJ fluid in NVE ensemble:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Δt = {dt}, n_steps = {n_steps}, total_time = {n_steps*dt:.3f} σ√(m/ε)\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Stride = {stride}, frames = {n_steps // stride}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run NVE from crystal initial condition\n",
    "pos = pos_fcc.copy()\n",
    "vel = vel_fcc.copy()\n",
    "forces = lj_force_pbc(pos, box)\n",
    "\n",
    "energies = []   # [KE, PE, Total]\n",
    "times = []\n",
    "frame_idx = 0\n",
    "n_frames = n_steps // stride\n",
    "traj_pos = np.zeros((n_frames + 1, n_atoms, 3))\n",
    "traj_vel = np.zeros((n_frames + 1, n_atoms, 3))\n",
    "\n",
    "traj_pos[0] = pos\n",
    "traj_vel[0] = vel\n",
    "\n",
    "for step in range(1, n_steps + 1):\n",
    "    pos, vel, forces = velocity_verlet(pos, vel, forces, box, dt, mass)\n",
    "    if step % stride == 0:\n",
    "        ke, pe, total_e = compute_energy(pos, vel, box, mass)\n",
    "        energies.append([ke, pe, total_e])\n",
    "        t = step * dt\n",
    "        times.append(t)\n",
    "        traj_pos[frame_idx] = pos\n",
    "        traj_vel[frame_idx] = vel\n",
    "        frame_idx += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "energies = np.array(energies)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Energy conservation analysis\n",
    "ke_init, pe_init, total_init = energies[0]\n",
    "ke_final, pe_final, total_final = energies[-1]\n",
    "E_drift = (total_final - total_init) / abs(total_init) * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n{'='*50}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  INITIAL:  KE = {ke_init:.4f}, PE = {pe_init:.4f}, E = {total_init:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  FINAL:    KE = {ke_final:.4f}, PE = {pe_final:.4f}, E = {total_final:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Drift:    ΔE = {total_final - total_init:.6f} ({abs(E_drift):.4f}%)\")\n",
    "print(f\"{'='*50}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Energy conservation plot saved to figs/03_energy_conservation.png\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Plot energy components over time\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Energy trace\n",
    "axes[0].plot(times, energies[:, 0], 'b-', label='KE', linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "axes[0].plot(times, energies[:, 1], 'r-', label='PE', linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "axes[0].plot(times, energies[:, 2], 'g-', label='E_total', linestyle='--', linewidth=2)\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Time (σ√(m/ε))')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Energy (ε)')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('NVE Energy Conservation')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "axes[0].annotate(f'Drift: {abs(E_drift):.4f}%', xy=(0.7, 0.05), xycoords='axes fraction',\n",
    "                 fontsize=11, bbox=dict(boxstyle='round', facecolor='white', alpha=0.8))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Energy drift at different time steps (convergence test)\n",
    "dts = [0.001, 0.002, 0.005, 0.01]\n",
    "drifts = []\n",
    "for dt_test in dts:\n",
    "    pos_t = pos_fcc.copy()\n",
    "    vel_t = vel_fcc.copy()\n",
    "    forces_t = lj_force_pbc(pos_t, box)\n",
    "    ke_i, pe_i, E_i = compute_energy(pos_t, vel_t, box, mass)\n",
    "    for _ in range(10000):\n",
    "        pos_t, vel_t, forces_t = velocity_verlet(pos_t, vel_t, forces_t, box, dt_test, mass)\n",
    "    ke_f, pe_f, E_f = compute_energy(pos_t, vel_t, box, mass)\n",
    "    drifts.append(abs(E_f - E_i) / abs(E_i))\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].semilogx(dts, drifts, 'ro-', linewidth=2, markersize=8)\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Time step Δt')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Relative energy drift')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Integration Convergence')\n",
    "axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('figs/03_energy_conservation.png', bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"Energy conservation plot saved to figs/03_energy_conservation.png\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Langevin Thermostat — Canonical Ensemble (NVT)\n",
    "\n",
    "The Langevin thermostat adds friction and stochastic noise to each particle:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$v(t+\\Delta t) = \\omega \\, v(t) + \\sqrt{\\frac{k_B T}{m}(1 - \\omega^2)} \\, \\eta$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $\\eta \\sim \\mathcal{N}(0,1)$ and $\\omega = e^{-\\gamma \\Delta t}$.\n",
    "\n",
    "This satisfies the fluctuation-dissipation theorem and correctly samples the canonical ensemble."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Langevin thermostat results saved to figs/03_langevin_thermostat.png\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Parameters\n",
    "gamma = 0.1        # Friction coefficient\n",
    "n_steps_l = 10000\n",
    "stride_l = 100\n",
    "t_max_l = n_steps_l // stride_l\n",
    "\n",
    "pos_l = pos_fcc.copy()\n",
    "vel_l = vel_fcc.copy()\n",
    "forces_l = lj_force_pbc(pos_l, box)\n",
    "\n",
    "temps_langevin = []\n",
    "temps_eq = []\n",
    "dofs = 3 * n_atoms - 3\n",
    "\n",
    "ke_ref = 0.5 * dofs  # E[kin] = ½ kT per dof, kT = 1 at T=1\n",
    "\n",
    "for step in range(n_steps_l):\n",
    "    pos_l, vel_l = langevin_thermostat(pos_l, vel_l, forces_l, gamma, T_target, dt)\n",
    "    forces_new = lj_force_pbc(pos_l, box)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Update positions with new forces\n",
    "    # Note: the thermostat updates positions + velocities in one call\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Compute instantaneous temperature\n",
    "    ke = compute_kinetic_energy(vel_l, mass)\n",
    "    T_inst = 2.0 * ke / dofs\n",
    "    temps_langevin.append(T_inst)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Every stride_l steps, compute running average\n",
    "    if step % stride_l == 0:\n",
    "        temps_eq.append(np.mean(temps_langevin[-min(step//stride_l, 1000):]))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    forces_l = forces_new\n",
    "\n",
    "temps_langevin = np.array(temps_langevin)\n",
    "temps_eq = np.array(temps_eq)\n",
    "t_eq = np.arange(len(temps_eq)) * dt * stride_l\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Instantaneous temperature: T = {temps_langevin.mean():.4f} ± {temps_langevin.std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Target temperature: T = {T_target}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Instantaneous temperature\n",
    "axes[0].plot(temps_langevin, 'b-', alpha=0.4, linewidth=0.5, label='instantaneous T')\n",
    "axes[0].axhline(T_target, color='r', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'T_target = {T_target}')\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Step')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Temperature (ε/kB)')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title(f'Langevin Thermostat (γ = {gamma})')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Running average\n",
    "axes[1].plot(t_eq, temps_eq, 'g-', linewidth=2, label='running average T')\n",
    "axes[1].axhline(T_target, color='r', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'T_target = {T_target}')\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Time (σ√(m/ε))')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Temperature (ε/kB)')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Temperature Relaxation')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('figs/03_langevin_thermostat.png', bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"Langevin thermostat results saved to figs/03_langevin_thermostat.png\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Andersen Thermostat — Stochastic Collisions\n",
    "\n",
    "The Andersen thermostat randomly reassigns velocities from the Maxwell-Boltzmann distribution:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$P_{\\text{collide}} = \\nu \\, \\Delta t$$\n",
    "\n",
    "For each particle, with this probability each step, its velocity is resampled from $\\mathcal{N}(0, kT/m)$.\n",
    "\n",
    "This gives the correct canonical ensemble but breaks momentum conservation (not good for transport properties)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Andersen thermostat results saved to figs/03_andersen_thermostat.png\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nu = 0.05  # Collision frequency\n",
    "n_steps_a = 10000\n",
    "stride_a = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "pos_a = pos_fcc.copy()\n",
    "vel_a = vel_fcc.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "temps_andersen = []\n",
    "temp_eq_a = []\n",
    "\n",
    "dof_count = np.ones(n_atoms)  # Track collided particles\n",
    "\n",
    "for step in range(n_steps_a):\n",
    "    vel_a = andersen_thermostat(vel_a, T_target, nu, dt)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ke = compute_kinetic_energy(vel_a, mass)\n",
    "    T_inst = 2.0 * ke / dofs\n",
    "    temps_andersen.append(T_inst)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if step % stride_a == 0:\n",
    "        n_recent = max(1, step // stride_a)\n",
    "        temp_eq_a.append(np.mean(temps_andersen[-max(1, 1000//stride_a):]))\n",
    "\n",
    "temps_andersen = np.array(temps_andersen)\n",
    "temp_eq_a = np.array(temp_eq_a)\n",
    "t_eq_a = np.arange(len(temp_eq_a)) * dt * stride_a\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Instantaneous temperature: T = {temps_andersen.mean():.4f} ± {temps_andersen.std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Target temperature: T = {T_target}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Collision probability per step: {nu*dt:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].plot(temps_andersen, 'm-', alpha=0.4, linewidth=0.5, label='instantaneous T')\n",
    "axes[0].axhline(T_target, color='r', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'T_target = {T_target}')\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Step')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Temperature')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title(f'Andersen Thermostat (ν = {nu})')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].plot(t_eq_a, temp_eq_a, 'c-', linewidth=2, label='running average T')\n",
    "axes[1].axhline(T_target, color='r', linestyle='--', linewidth=2)\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Time')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Temperature')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Temperature Relaxation')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('figs/03_andersen_thermostat.png', bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"Andersen thermostat results saved to figs/03_andersen_thermostat.png\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Temperature Comparison — Langevin vs Andersen\n",
    "\n",
    "Both thermostats should converge to the target temperature, but with different relaxation dynamics:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Temperature comparison plot saved to figs/03_temp_comparison.png\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compare equilibrium temperatures\n",
    "langevin_final = temps_langevin[int(len(temps_langevin)*0.75):]\n",
    "andersen_final = temps_andersen[int(len(temps_andersen)*0.75):]\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].hist(temps_andersen, bins=80, alpha=0.6, color='m', label='Andersen', density=True)\n",
    "axes[0].hist(temps_langevin, bins=80, alpha=0.6, color='g', label='Langevin', density=True)\n",
    "axes[0].axvline(T_target, color='r', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'T_target = {T_target}')\n",
    "axes[0].axvline(langevin_final.mean(), color='g', linestyle=':', alpha=0.7, label=f'Langevin mean = {langevin_final.mean():.3f}')\n",
    "axes[0].axvline(andersen_final.mean(), color='m', linestyle=':', alpha=0.7, label=f'Andersen mean = {andersen_final.mean():.3f}')\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Temperature')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('PDF')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Equilibrium Temperature Distributions')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
