    "## 7. RDF — Radial Distribution Function\n",
    "\n",
    "The RDF $g(r)$ describes the structure of the fluid:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$g(r) = \\frac{\\langle n(r) \\rangle}{4\\pi r^2 \\rho \\, dr}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "For an ideal gas, $g(r) = 1$ everywhere. For a liquid, it shows:\n",
    "- A sharp peak at $r \\approx \\sigma$ (contact distance)\n",
    "- A secondary peak (second coordination shell)\n",
    "- Convergence to 1 at large r"
   ]
  },
